# MarianMT-Hindi-English-NMT

🚧 **Research Project | Manuscript Under Preparation**

## Overview

MarianMT-Hindi-English-NMT is a research-oriented Neural Machine Translation (NMT) framework designed to improve Hindi-to-English translation through transformer-based contextual learning. The framework leverages the MarianMT architecture, attention-based sequence modeling, transfer learning, and fine-tuning on the IIT Bombay Hindi-English Parallel Corpus to generate fluent, semantically accurate, and context-aware translations.

Unlike traditional Rule-Based Machine Translation (RBMT) and Statistical Machine Translation (SMT) systems, the proposed framework utilizes self-attention and cross-attention mechanisms to capture long-range dependencies, contextual meaning, and grammatical consistency during translation generation.

