## Key Findings

- Achieved a BLEU score of **46.80** on Hindi-to-English translation tasks.
- Generated context-aware and semantically coherent English translations.
- Improved translation fluency compared to traditional RBMT and SMT approaches.
- Leveraged transfer learning through MarianMT fine-tuning.
- Demonstrated strong performance across conversational, cultural, temporal, conditional, and interrogative sentence structures.
- Reduced contextual ambiguity using transformer-based attention mechanisms.

---

## Research Contributions

- Developed a transformer-based Hindi-to-English Neural Machine Translation framework using MarianMT.
- Fine-tuned a pretrained MarianMT model on the IIT Bombay Hindi-English Parallel Corpus.
- Integrated self-attention and cross-attention mechanisms for contextual translation generation.
- Evaluated translation quality using BLEU, TER, and ChrF metrics.
- Proposed a scalable framework for multilingual communication applications.

